					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">byuu wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Cydrak figured it out, added split-screen too, cool!<br /><br /><br /><br />Inside chr_read:<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">&nbsp; if(in_frame == false) {<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; if(addr &amp; 0x2000) return ciram_read(addr);<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; return 0x00;<br />&nbsp; }</div><br /><br />The game reads the nametable out of CHR ROM, so we need:<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">&nbsp; if(in_frame == false) {<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; if(addr &amp; 0x2000) return ciram_read(addr);<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; return board.chrrom.read(chr_active ? chr_bg_addr(addr) : chr_sprite_addr(addr));<br />&nbsp; }</div><br /><br /><br /><br />I even tried returning rand() instead of 0x00 and didn't notice a visual change, so I didn't suspect it was a problem.<br /><br /><br /><br />Would be a good thing to note in the Wiki, assuming I didn't just overlook it.</div><br /><br />byuu,<br /><br />I am having exactly the same issue that you described in this thread.  The introduction animation of Uchuu Keibitai SDF looks screwed up, but the game itself seems to play correctly.<br /><br />Can you elaborate on your solution to the issue?  I do not fully understand your code.  Did you update the wiki with the missing information?<br /><br />Thanks for your help.<br /><br />Edit: After carefully studying your code, I think I solved it!  We need to add something like this to the wiki:<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">if (inFrame ? spriteSize8x16 ? spriteTile : useChrSetA : useChrSetA) {<br />&nbsp; // read from CHR ROM set A<br />} else {<br />&nbsp; // read from CHR ROM set B<br />}</div><br /><br />The above code is used in a VRAM read when the address &lt; $2000.  inFrame is described in the MMC5 docs.  As far as I understand it, it basically means if you are not in VBlank.  spriteSize8x16 is clear.  spriteTile is set if PPU is retrieving a sprite tile.  The MMC5 chips maybe able to figure this out using counters, but I cheated and I just had my simulated PPU provide that information anytime it accessed VRAM.  useChrSetA is set when the chr A registers are used (described in the doc).  <br /><br />Studying the docs suggested that I just needed:<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">if (spriteSize8x16 ? spriteTile : useChrSetA) {<br />&nbsp; // read from CHR ROM set A<br />} else {<br />&nbsp; // read from CHR ROM set B<br />}</div><br /><br />But, the inFrame check is necessary.</div>

